                      *S*imple *P*lotting *T*ool
                      --------------------------

Contact information is available at:
------------------------------------

Ethan Burns <http://www.cs.unh.edu/~eaburns>
Jordan Thayer <http://www.cs.unh.edu/~jtd7>


Dependencies
------------
* lacaml (which depends on lapack, which depends on libgfortran)
* cairo-ocaml (which depends on Cairo: http://cairographics.org/)
* lablgtk

Getting the dependencies for compilation on Ubuntu (not well tested):
    apt-get install ocaml-findlib
    apt-get install libcairo-ocaml-dev
    apt-get install liblapack-dev
    apt-get install gfortran

    Download and install lacaml
    (http://ocaml.info/home/ocaml_sources.html) from source as per the
    instructions (make ; make install).  On a 64-bit system, you will
    need to copy or link the lacaml directory that is installed to
    your /usr/lib64/ocaml directory.


To build spt-it-out:
--------------------

ocamlbuild src/spt-it-out/spt_it_out.byte

or (for native)

ocamlbuild src/spt-it-out/spt_it_out.native


To build simple_plotting_tool the library
-----------------------------------------

ocamlbuild simple_plotting_tool.cma

or (for native)

ocamlbuild simple_plotting_tool.cmxa


Install it with:
mkdir <ocaml directory>/simple_plotting_tool
cp _build/simple_plotting_tool* <ocaml directory>/simple_plotting_tool
